February 5, 2026
HOUSE
RESOLUTION No. 26
Introduced by: Smith H, Goss-Reaves, Ireland, Teshka,
Greene, Aylesworth, VanNatter, Miller D, Lopez, Lauer,
Heaton, Soliday, King, Morris, Bascom, Isa, Olthoff, Pierce K,
Yocum, Ledbetter, Baird
____________________________________
February 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Ways and
Means.
1 A HOUSE RESOLUTION urging the Indiana General
2 Assembly to prioritize legislation during the 2027 budget year,
3 establishing property tax credits for unemployable Hoosier
4 veterans who are permanently and totally disabled.
5 Whereas, Twenty-two states across the nation have enacted
6 property tax benefits for their permanently disabled veterans,
7 recognizing the obligation owed to those who have borne the
8 most significant burdens of military service;
9 Whereas, These veterans often rely solely on VA disability
10 compensation and Social Security benefits for the duration of
11 their lives, making financial insecurity a persistent and serious
12 concern;
HR 26—RR 4504/DI hf

2
1 Whereas, Such a credit should be recognized as repayment
2 of a national debt owed to the men and women who have
3 sacrificed their health and livelihood in defense of the United
4 States;
5 Whereas, Establishing credit would strengthen Indiana’s
6 position as a veteran-friendly state, encouraging newly
7 discharged service members to settle in Indiana, and
8 supporting efforts to prevent military and veteran suicide; and
9 Whereas, Granting this support will offer disabled veterans
10 meaningful encouragement and assurance that the elected
11 representatives of Indiana recognize the profound sacrifices
12 they have made on behalf of the nation: Therefore,
13 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
14 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
15 SECTION 1. That the Indiana House of Representative
16 urges the General Assembly to pursue, during the 2027 budget
17 year, legislation that prioritizes the establishment of a property
18 tax credit for permanently and totally disabled veterans.
19 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
20 Representatives shall transmit a copy of this resolution to the
21 Governor, the Chair of the House Ways and Means Committee,
22 the Chair of the Senate Appropriations Committee, and the
23 Indiana Department of Veterans Affairs.
HR 26—RR 4504/DI hf

